<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">jtpriest</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just got my Aegis this morning and proved, fairly conclusively, that the faction bug is now fixed.  All told, I turned in 152 bone chips, 42 gp and 30 sashes. The first 16 sashes got me to warmly, the next 12 got me to where he would give the quest.  I went back to the boneyard and verified that killing a Putrid only gave a faction hit with Bloodsabres.  I turned in 2 more sashes for luck and then gave Cameland the scythe. He asked for the heart. I gave it to him and got the Aegis.  I never even bothered with the fish.  Hope this helps.<P>------------------<BR>Jhonas Tsalk<BR>Lvl 52 Dwarven Bandaid<BR>Erollisi Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zifnab</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I saw Yellabeard camping Grimmie AGAIN because his warmly faction wasn't good enough and the quest giver ate his Scythe.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Darwind</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">BUT   when did he turn in his items ??<P>------------------<BR><B>Darwind Healem </B><BR>Level 42<BR>Primary Healer in Rane’s Raiders<P>Keeper of the Paw<BR>Seeker of the Aegis<BR>Master Brewer<BR>Master Fletcher<BR>Grand Master Blacksmith<BR>Halfling Cleric of the Krieger<P>     <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>May Tunare always gaze upon thee, my child<HR></BLOCKQUOTE></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Blammo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Has his level / MR been buffed? What did you notice? How did you smack him down? How long did you have to camp for the Dead V?<P>Thanks<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Troas Merwind</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">For the past three weeks I'd been making a habit of logging out at the Grimrot camp, so I never camped him as much as kept checking in on him.  However, based on reports from other clerics on Saryrn, I'd estimate spawns every RL day or two.<P>The dead version was green to me at 49th.  Two banishes were unresisted for 585 each, leaving him no visible health.  A little mace work, and then I removed the misshapen heart that he wasn't using any longer.  Turned in a few more fish for luck and now I've got a shiny new aegis on my back!  On the down side, I'm down to dubious with the corrupt guards - need to go back to highhold pass I guess to work on faction.<P>------------------<BR>Troas Merwind<BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR>Saryrn</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
